In this tutorial you can learn - step by step - how to create a simple 
<a href='explanation/web_application' target='_blank' class='dialogLink'>web application</a> 
using 
<a href='explanation/java_servlets_technology' target='_blank' class='dialogLink'>Java Servlets Technology</a> 
and 
<a href='explanation/jsp' target='_blank' class='dialogLink'>JSP</a>. 
An example application will retrieve user`s name from one 
<a href='explanation/web_page' target='_blank' class='dialogLink'>web page</a> 
and display on the second page after the sentence: 'Hello World' (view demo). 
This used Java Servlet Technology is the part of 
<a href='explanation/j2ee' target='_blank' class='dialogLink'>J2EE</a> 
and it`s a base for creating web applications in 
<a href='explanation/java_language' target='_blank' class='dialogLink'>Java language</a>. 